04/09/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- SFOR Commander Lieutenant General William Ward gave high marks Wednesday (3 September) to the work of the Bulgarian unit at Camp Butmir. 
Deputy Chief of General Staff of the Bulgarian Army Lieutenant General Atanas Zapryanov met with Ward while visiting BiH to inspect the Bulgarian contingent there. 
The company at Camp Butmir has been in the country since July, guarding the headquarters, patrolling the area and maintaining a rapid reaction group on 24-hour alert. 
Another unit, a mechanised platoon, is based at Camp Bugojno and is responsible for the municipality of Gornji Vakuf. 
(BTA - 03/09/03)
